Clear instructions: Update version in ONE place

Add this variable at the top of sw.js and it will control everything automatically.

---

1. sw.js - Replace the top section (lines 1-5)

Current code:

```javascript
// sw.js - Production-ready offline-first service worker for AHCPMG301 Weed Training

const CACHE_NAME = 'weed-control-v4';
const OFFLINE_URL = '/offline.html';
```

Replace with:

```javascript
// sw.js - Production-ready offline-first service worker for AHCPMG301 Weed Training

// ⚡ UPDATE THIS ONE NUMBER WHEN YOU MAKE CHANGES ⚡
const APP_VERSION = '2.0.0';
// ================================================

const CACHE_NAME = `weed-control-v${APP_VERSION.replace(/\./g, '-')}`;
const OFFLINE_URL = '/offline.html';
```

---

2. index.html - Add version to footer

Find this section near the bottom (around line 1240):

Current code:

```html
<footer class="footer">
    <span>© AHCPMG301 · Prediction-First Learning · Tasmanian Edition</span>
    <span>Remember: Learning happens in the gap between prediction and reality</span>
    <span>Field judgement > content knowledge | Biosecurity Act 2019 (TAS)</span>
</footer>
```

Replace with:

```html
<footer class="footer">
    <span>© AHCPMG301 · Prediction-First Learning · Tasmanian Edition</span>
    <span>Version <span id="appVersion">2.0.0</span> | Remember: Learning happens in the gap between prediction and reality</span>
    <span>Field judgement > content knowledge | Biosecurity Act 2019 (TAS)</span>
</footer>
```

Then add this script before the closing </body> tag (around line 1280, after the service worker registration):

```html
<script>
// Display version from service worker
const versionSpan = document.getElementById('appVersion');
if (versionSpan) {
    fetch('/sw.js')
        .then(response => response.text())
        .then(text => {
            const versionMatch = text.match(/APP_VERSION = ['"]([^'"]+)['"]/);
            if (versionMatch) {
                versionSpan.textContent = versionMatch[1];
            }
        })
        .catch(() => {
            // Keep default version if can't fetch
        });
}
</script>
```

